divs: Sighting DetailsI was sitting at the light coming out of the Home Depot on Route 70 in Cherry Hill. It was a gorgeous day and there was little cloud cover. I happened to look up towards the southeast and saw an unidentified flying object. I can't really estimate distance... it was probably a few miles away at a height of at least 10,000 feet. It was a silver cigar-shaped object. Pointed on both ends. I supposed it could have been a flying saucer being viewed from the side. It was moving at a steady, non-hurried pace for about 4 seconds and then it simply disappeared. It didn't accelerate suddenly or change directions - it simply popped out of existence. I kept staring at that part of the sky for another 30 seconds but saw nothing else. I don't believe this was a plane or a jet. I've seen jets leave vapor trails and there was none. There wasn't a cloud in that part of the sky. No other aircraft. It was a silver object moving in a general northern direction and after a few seconds - POOF. It was just gone. I keep an open mind with regards to UFO's. This is the first time I've seen an object in the sky I could not identify. Hoping some other people may have spotted this object for corraberation.
